# No sudo on training / lab servers

The maintainer may use shared lab machines (e.g. SSH training hosts) **without `sudo`**.

## Do not assume

- `sudo apt install`, `sudo reboot`, `sudo nvidia-smi --gpu-reset`
- `sudo nvidia-cuda-mps-control` or other NVIDIA daemon control
- System-wide `pip` / PEP 668 overrides (`--break-system-packages`)
- `chown`/`chmod` on system directories

## Prefer instead

- **Python:** `python3 -m venv ~/.venv-…` and `venv/bin/python -m pip` (no sudo).
- **GPU / MPS / driver errors (e.g. CUDA 805):** resolution usually needs **admin/IT**; suggest **contacting lab support** with `nvidia-smi` + the full error, not sudo-only fixes.
- **Workaround without admin:** `export CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=` for CPU-only runs when GPU init fails.
- **System packages:** point to **admin docs** or user-space installs (`pip`/`conda` in home) only.

When giving runbooks for training or server workflows in this repo, use steps that work in an **unprivileged** shell unless the user says they have elevated access.
